# [WIMSE](../wg/wimse.html)

## Summary

The WIMSE (Workload Identity in a Multi System Environment) Working Group met at IETF 126 in Vienna. The session was divided into two main parts: progress updates on active working group documents that are approaching or currently in Working Group Last Call (WGLC), followed by presentations and discussions on new work proposals related to workload identity, trust domains, attestation, and AI agent security. 

Key outcomes included plans to schedule WGLCs for several foundational specifications, including HTTP signatures, MTLS, and workload identifiers. There was also strong interest in exploring trust domain discovery, workload identity federation (WIF), and the standardization of security frameworks for AI agents.

